We know that $\cos(\theta) = -1$ when the angle $\theta$ is $\pi$ radians (180 degrees). Since the question implies radians (as is standard in IB calculus and functions), we use $\pi$.

$$
\begin{aligned}
7q &= \pi \\
q &= \frac{\pi}{7}
\end{aligned}
$$
